⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Sheeana
node D1 · D1 · ⟦Sheeana:D1:075efd⟧

WHO   — Sheeana — the girl who commands the worms
WHAT  — A desert child of Rakis who can command the sandworms, the last fragments of the God Emperor, which will not harm her.
WHERE — D1 · Dune  Framework inputs: The desert of Rakis and the late Sisterhood — Heretics of Dune and Chapterhouse  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Taken in by the Bene Gesserit, she becomes central to the Sisterhood's survival and to the seeding of new deserts and worms.
HOW   — She walks among the worms and they obey, sparing her where they spare no other, a living bridge between the worm and the human.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  She walks the sand and the worms bow; in her the desert keeps faith with the human.

